## 15. DEPLOYMENT & ENVIRONMENT

### Service ports (local dev)

| Service | HTTP | gRPC | Metrics |
|---|---|---|---|
| API Gateway | 3000 | — | 9000 |
| Orders Service | 3001 | — | 9001 |
| Payment Settlement | 3002 | — | 9002 |
| AI Chatbot | 3003 | — | 9003 |
| Fulfillment | 3004 | — | 9004 |
| Notification | 3005 | — | 9005 |
| Pricing Engine (Rust) | — | 50051 | 9090 |
| Fraud Detection (Rust) | — | 50052 | 9091 |
| Chain Listener (Rust) | 4000 (webhook) | — | 9092 |

### Health checks — every service

```typescript
// NestJS — required on every service
@Get('/health')
health(): { status: string; timestamp: string } {
  return { status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() };
}
```

```rust
// Rust — axum health route on separate port
async fn health() -> impl IntoResponse {
    Json(json!({ "status": "ok", "timestamp": Utc::now().to_rfc3339() }))
}
```

### Rules
- Every service has `/health` — load balancer and k8s liveness probe target
- Graceful shutdown: drain in-flight requests before exiting — never SIGKILL in production
- Environment variables for all config — no config files with secrets in Docker images
- Resource limits on every container: CPU and memory — prevent one service starving others
- Separate ECS task definitions / k8s deployments per service — never colocate

---

## 16. WHAT CURSOR SHOULD NEVER DO

- Never use `float` or `double` for any monetary amount
- Never hardcode Paystack keys, wallet addresses, or RPC URLs
- Never write a DB migration that drops a column without a multi-step deploy plan
- Never add `console.log` with full webhook payloads
- Never bypass the idempotency gate "just for testing"
- Never use `Math.random()` for anything in payment flows
- Never process a payment event without first validating the order exists and is in the correct state
- Never return a 500 with a raw error message or stack trace to an external client
- Never add a new chain adapter without implementing the full `ChainListener` trait
- Never store a gift code in plain text — always `code_enc` via KMS
- Never commit `.env` files, private keys, or seed phrases

---

## 17. CODE REVIEW CHECKLIST

Before raising a PR on payment-critical code, verify:

- [ ] No floating point arithmetic on monetary values
- [ ] Idempotency key present for any operation triggered by an external event
- [ ] State machine transition validated before DB write
- [ ] Webhook signature verification in place
- [ ] No secrets in code or logs
- [ ] Error path tested — not just happy path
- [ ] Structured log fields correct and complete
- [ ] No raw Prisma errors returned to client
- [ ] New Redis keys have explicit TTLs
- [ ] gRPC calls have timeout set
- [ ] New Rust code: `clippy` clean, no `unwrap()` in hot paths
